    "id": "F-001",
    "severity": "Critical",
    "confidence": "high",
    "title": "Public flash-loan entrypoint lets arbitrary contracts impersonate the DSA and drain connector-held whitelisted assets",
    "locations": [
      "0x9f54e8eaa9658316bb8006e03fff1cb191aafbe6/contracts/connectors/ConnectorDeleverageParaswap.sol:111",
      "0x9f54e8eaa9658316bb8006e03fff1cb191aafbe6/contracts/connectors/ConnectorDeleverageParaswap.sol:112",
      "0x9f54e8eaa9658316bb8006e03fff1cb191aafbe6/contracts/connectors/ConnectorDeleverageParaswap.sol:262",
      "0x9f54e8eaa9658316bb8006e03fff1cb191aafbe6/contracts/connectors/ConnectorDeleverageParaswap.sol:349",
      "0x9f54e8eaa9658316bb8006e03fff1cb191aafbe6/contracts/connectors/ConnectorDeleverageParaswap.sol:350"
    ],
    "claim": "`flashloanReq` is callable by anyone and blindly records `msg.sender` as the trusted `_dsaAddress`. During the Aave callback, the connector grants that address allowance over the flash-loaned assets and calls `executeAction` on it, so an attacker-controlled contract can pull tokens out of the connector.",
    "impact": "Any whitelisted token balance already sitting on the connector can be stolen. An attacker can flash-borrow the same token, siphon the borrowed amount during `executeAction`, and let Aave repayment consume the connector's pre-existing balance, fully draining stranded user/protocol funds.",
    "paths": [
      "Attacker deploys a contract that implements `executeAction` and steals approved tokens with `transferFrom`.",
      "If the connector holds stranded whitelisted token `T`, attacker calls `flashloanReq(false, [T], [amount], [0], [], [], [])` from that contract and pre-funds the flash-loan premium.",
      "Inside `repayAllDebtAssetsWithFlashLoan`, the connector approves the attacker contract for `amount` of `T` and calls its `executeAction`.",
      "The attacker contract pulls the flash-loaned `T`; Aave then repays itself from the connector's existing `T` balance, leaving the attacker with the stolen tokens."
    ]
  },
