    "claim": "The swap path trusts fully user-controlled `srcToken`, `tokenTransferProxy`, `paraSwapContract`, and `paraswapCallData`. The connector approves the chosen proxy and then performs an arbitrary external call, with no validation that the addresses are genuine Paraswap contracts or that the call performs the intended swap.",
    "impact": "Any ERC20 balance present on the connector, including non-whitelisted tokens or accidental transfers, can be stolen by an attacker-controlled proxy/target pair. This bypasses the multisig-only recovery path in `withdrawToken`.",
    "paths": [
      "Attacker identifies token `X` currently held by the connector.",
      "Attacker calls public `flashloanReq` with a minimal flash-loan asset for repayment and a crafted `swapData` entry where `srcToken = X`, `tokenTransferProxy = attacker`, `paraSwapContract = attacker`.",
      "During `deloopAllCollaterals`, the connector approves the attacker for `X` and immediately calls the attacker contract.",
      "The attacker contract uses the fresh approval to `transferFrom` all `X` out of the connector, while the unrelated flash loan is repaid normally."
    ]
